# .cursorrules
This is an Ayurvedic text mining MVP project.

Tech stack:
- Python 3.10+
- Flask for backend
- spaCy for NLP
- Neo4j for knowledge graph
- PubChem REST API

Key concepts:
- Extract herb names, properties (rasa, guna, virya, vipaka), and therapeutic actions from Ayurvedic texts
- Rasa = taste (6 types: sweet, sour, salty, pungent, bitter, astringent)
- Guna = qualities (hot/cold, heavy/light, etc.)
- Build knowledge graph connecting herbs to properties and modern phytochemicals

Code style:
- Use type hints
- Follow PEP 8
- Add docstrings to all functions
- Error handling with try-except blocks
